Catherine WILSON, etc., Appellants, v. Raymond A. CARROLL et al., Appellees. No. 7792. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Oct. 17, 1935. Charles E. McGinnis, W. Frank Shelley, and C. C. Caswell, all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. John Q. Adams, Vernon Gray, William L. Kuehn, and Franz R. Sachse, all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellees.

Before WILBUR, MATHEWS, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the record and briefs filed herein, and after oral argument of counsel for respective parties, ordered, decree of District Court, affirmed; that a decree be filed and entered accordingly; mandate issued in accordance with rule 32.
